The Buccaneers held a press briefing to announce the new coach following spate of poor results in the league. JOHANNESBURG Kjell Jonevret has been revealed as the new coach of Orlando Pirates on a three-year contract.The Buccaneers held a press briefing to announce the new coach following a spate of poor results in the league.The post was left vacant by Muhsin Ertugral, who resigned late last year after they suffered heavy loss to SuperSport United. Pirates chairperson Dr Irvin Khoza also confrimed the release of Ghanaian defender Edwin Gyimah. Bradly Carnell has also left the club having accepted an offer abroad.